      "writtenOn": "2021-06-15T07:45:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e shouldn\u0027t this all happen before we decide how we are going to sample the dst and setup the view?\n\nIt could, but setupDstProxyView will also split the render task if a DMSAA attachment is involved, so in both cases we end up splitting the opsTask. I added tests to catch both scenarios.\n\n\u003e Like if I used a bunch of texture barriers in previous draws. And now I get a draw that wants to use DMSAA but doesn\u0027t need the dst itself. I still need to break up the OpsTask \n\nThat\u0027s exactly the scenario that this \"else\" branch is covering, and there is a new test for it.",
      "parentUuid": "3df22787_9f0e1e48",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1929,
        "startChar": 7,
