        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-14T17:16:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What if we wrote this whole section like (lots of partial pseudocode here).\n\nbool drawsToMSAA \u003d this-\u003egetOpsTask()-\u003eusesMSAASurface();\n// This caps call will return kNone if drawsToMSAA is true and we don\u0027t support\n// renderToTexture. If we do support renderToTexture it may return kTexBarrier if\n// they are supported (and in gl the rt is a texture)\nauto dstSampleFlags \u003d this-\u003ecaps()-\u003egetDstSampleFlagsForProxy(rtProxy, drawsToMSAA);\n\n// First check if we can sample directly the color attachment as either a texture\n// or an input attachment. In either case the flags will always have returned\n// kTexBarrier\nif (dstSampleFlags \u0026 kTexBarrier) {\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetProxyView(this-\u003ereadSurfaceView());\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetOffset(0, 0);\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetDstSampleFlags(dstSampleFlags);\n    return;\n}\n\nSkASSERT(dstSampleFlags \u003d\u003d kNone);\n\n// To sample the dst we must use a separate surface for the color attachment.\n// First if the color attachment is MSAA we will try to use a resolve attachment\n// as our texture. Otherwise we will have to do a copy to scratch texture.\nauto resolveTex \u003d rtProxy-\u003easTextureProxy();\nif (drawsToMSAA \u0026\u0026 resolveTex) {\n    // If we had renderToTexture and barrier support we should have been able to\n    // use a barrier\n    SkASSERT(!renderToTexture || !barrierSupport);\n  \n    if (!first draw into opsTask) {\n        this-\u003ereplaceOpsTask()-\u003esetCannotMergeBackward();\n    }\n    \n    if (!usingDMSAA) { // so using normal msaa\n        // Does this have to go before the replaceOpsTask above?? I\u0027m not sure\n        // what our required ordering is to make sure the resolve task gets\n        // placed between the two opsTasks.\n        this-\u003eaddResolveTask(resolveTex, rt);\n    }\n    \n    // I understand that these three lines look the same as the texBarrier block\n    // above. However, that is just because right now we get the RT tex and\n    // resolve texture from the same object today. In the not too far off future\n    // these may come from different objects. Also I think organizing the code\n    // this way makes it much clearer the logic that we are trying to do.\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetProxyView(this-\u003ereadSurfaceView());\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetOffset(0, 0);\n    dstProxyView-\u003esetDstSampleFlags(dstSampleFlags);\n    return;\n}\n\n// All our current copy code.",
      "revId": "5981f6a17e4bb5cd80b5f91e9ce026b765dd83b5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
